\f1\b\fs48 \cf2 \strokec2 Goal Evolution in Deterministic Narrative Simulation: Restoring Structural Quality Through Coordinated Agent Adaptation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 Abstract\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 Current approaches to generative narrative rely primarily on Large Language Models (LLMs) executing sequential token prediction, resulting in stories that are locally coherent but often globally episodic. We introduce 
\f2\i Lorien
\f0\i0 , a simulation-first narrative engine that inverts this paradigm by decoupling structural generation from prose rendering. Lorien utilizes a deterministic, utility-weighted multi-agent simulation to generate event sequences, which are then evaluated by a grammar-constrained search to extract mathematically valid dramatic arcs. While this architecture achieves a 98% structural validity baseline in isolated scenarios, sequentially chaining simulations with persistent world states (canon) results in monotonic structural degradation (~0.015 mean arc score decay per episode). Through zero-cost computational ablation studies, we diagnose this decay as 
\f2\i epistemic ossification
\f0\i0 \'97a state of information equilibrium where agents continue to execute obsolete objective functions after core secrets are universally revealed. We demonstrate that while forcing unilateral belief mutation cannot rescue structural tension, coordinated 
\f2\i Goal Evolution
\f0\i0 \'97updating agent utility vectors to align with the new epistemology\'97restores structural quality to within 0.006 of pristine baseline levels. Furthermore, we demonstrate that uncoordinated (asymmetrical) agent evolution actively breaks the structural validity of unaligned agents, proving the network dependency of dramatic structure. Finally, we propose a discretized "Stance Matrix" to operationalize procedural objective-function adaptation while protecting the mathematical integrity of the simulation from stochastic LLM generation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
