\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 \strokec2 1. Introduction: The Crystallization Paradigm\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 The prevailing method for generating computational narrative utilizes Large Language Models (LLMs) to autoregressively predict the next most likely token. While this produces excellent prose texture and local logical consistency, it fundamentally struggles with global structural relationships. Deep fiction relies on "cathedral" architecture: promises seeded early and resolved late, dramatic irony driven by persistent information asymmetry, and climaxes forced by intersecting, mutually exclusive character constraints. Sequential token generation produces an "episodic" architecture where events happen 
\f2\i after
\f0\i0  one another, rather than 
\f2\i because
\f0\i0  of one another.\
We present an alternative generative paradigm called 
\f2\i crystallization
\f0\i0 , instantiated in the Lorien narrative engine. Lorien treats structural narrative generation as a deterministic constraint-satisfaction problem, entirely independent of LLM text generation. In this paradigm, global coherence emerges from mathematical constraint resolution rather than local linguistic prediction.\
However, attempting to chain these discrete simulations into serialized structures (e.g., a continuous "season" of episodes sharing a continuous canon) reveals a fundamental boundary in simulation-based storytelling: as agents interact, information is universally distributed. Secrets are revealed, tension potential is spent, and the simulation suffers from monotonic structural degradation. This paper investigates the underlying computational mechanics of this degradation and proves that coordinated agent goal-evolution is required to maintain structural validity in persistent computational narratives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 2. System Architecture and Baseline Stability\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 The Lorien engine operates via a strict separation of concerns, executing in four discrete phases:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Simulation Layer:
\f0\b0  A pure Python, deterministic multi-agent simulation. Given a starting seed and a \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 WorldCanon\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  (inherited world state), $N$ agents driven by numeric utility vectors (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 goals\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 relationships\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 commitments\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ) interact across discrete locations. A standard run produces ~200 discrete events (e.g., \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 CHAT\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 REVEAL\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 CONFLICT\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 CATASTROPHE\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ).\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Metrics Layer:
\f0\b0  A mathematical evaluation of the event sequence calculating 
\f2\i Tension
\f0\i0  (accumulated conflict pressure) and 
\f2\i Dramatic Irony
\f0\i0  (the topological gap between an agent's internal \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 claim_states\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  and the established objective truth).\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Extraction Layer (Rashomon):
\f0\b0  A grammar-constrained search algorithm that parses the event sequence for a structurally valid protagonist arc. The grammar enforces strict beat topologies: 
\f2\i Setup
\f0\i0  must precede 
\f2\i Complication
\f0\i0 ; 
\f2\i Escalation
\f0\i0  must precede a singular 
\f2\i Turning Point
\f0\i0 , followed by 
\f2\i Consequence
\f0\i0 . The system utilizes "Rashomon Extraction" to extract up to six concurrent, genuinely distinct protagonist arcs from the exact same objective event sequence.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Narration Layer:
\f0\b0  An LLM acts solely as a rendering engine to translate the mathematically validated arcs into prose.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Baseline Validation:
\f0\b0  In a 50-seed parameter sweep of a highly constrained 6-agent "Dinner Party" scenario (involving concealed infidelity and financial fraud), the Rashomon extractor produced valid arcs in 294/300 cases (98%), yielding a mean valid arc score of 0.694. This establishes that the beat grammar robustly captures universal topologies of dramatic structure.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 3. The Autopsy of Narrative Heat Death\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 To achieve episodic chaining (Story A $\\rightarrow$ B $\\rightarrow$ C $\\rightarrow$ D $\\rightarrow$ E), Lorien persists a \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 WorldCanon\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  object between simulation runs, transferring accumulated physical "texture" facts and simulation state (location tension residue, agent belief states).\
While LLM-generated texture facts accumulated healthily (0 $\\rightarrow$ 69 facts across 5 steps), empirical testing proved them structurally inert. Inherited simulation state, however, resulted in a strict monotonic degradation of the mean valid arc score. A 4-chain seed-order experiment isolated the variable, revealing a decay rate of ~0.015 per chain step: Depth 0 (Score: 0.696) degraded to Depth 4 (Score: 0.637). Attempts to cure this via mathematical float decay (reducing starting tension residue) produced zero structural effect.\
We diagnosed this state-space collapse as 
\f1\b Epistemic Ossification
\f0\b0  (Information Equilibrium). Lorien\'92s tension math leverages information asymmetry. By Depth 2 of the simulation chain, major secrets (e.g., the illicit affair, an ongoing investigation) transitioned from \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 unknown\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 believes_true\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  for all 6 agents. The potential energy of the system reached zero, yet agents continued attempting to execute their original, obsolete utility functions (e.g., the guilty party's goal vector still heavily weighted \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 secrecy\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ). The engine accurately modeled the resulting structural incoherence, producing low-scoring, repetitive interactions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 4. Experiment 1: The Causal Interface (Belief Perturbation)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 To prove that categorical \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 claim_states\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  are the causal interface governing the simulation's structure, and to test if injecting new information asymmetry could rescue the score, we conducted a zero-cost, headless perturbation experiment at Depth 2.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Methodology:
\f0\b0  We intercepted the exhausted \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 WorldCanon\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  before Story C (Baseline Score: 0.668). We manually mutated a single categorical belief: shifting the protagonist's (Thorne's) knowledge of a peripheral secret (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 secret_embezzle_01\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ) from \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 unknown\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 suspects\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , effectively simulating a sudden realization.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Results & Analysis:
\f0\b0 \
