\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Causal Proof:
\f0\b0  System trace logs recorded 13,895 discrete reads of \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 claim_states\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  during the tick loop, confirming it as the primary causal interface. The perturbation caused event divergence at tick 0, proving instantaneous deterministic sensitivity. A control mutation of a structurally inert belief produced zero divergence.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Score Penalty:
\f0\b0  Despite the sensitivity, the global mean arc score actively dropped from the baseline 0.668 to 0.628 ($\\Delta$ -0.040). Thorne's personal arc dropped precipitously from 0.709 to 0.550.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Discussion:
\f0\b0  The mathematical extraction grammar correctly penalized the perturbation. Thorne's core utility objective was defined as 
\f2\i "Maintain normalcy."
\f0\i0  Forcing an agent whose primary reality (his marriage) had just been publicly destroyed to abruptly investigate a peripheral white-collar crime was recognized as structurally incoherent\'97forensic noise rather than valid dramatic escalation. Adding a peripheral mystery cannot fix an exhausted narrative ecosystem if the core agent objectives remain mismatched with the emotional reality of the world state.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 5. Experiment 2: Coordinated Goal Evolution\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 Following the failure of belief perturbation, we hypothesized that structural validity could be restored by 
\f1\b Goal Evolution
\f0\b0 : updating the agents' underlying objective functions to align with the new, post-revelation epistemology.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Methodology:
\f0\b0  Using the identical, exhausted Depth 2 canon, we intercepted the simulation instantiation. Rather than mutating belief states, we mutated the target weights and core goals of the agents (e.g., shifting the guilty party from 
\f2\i Concealment
\f0\i0  to 
\f2\i Survival
\f0\i0 ; shifting the betrayed from 
\f2\i Maintain Normalcy
\f0\i0  to 
\f2\i Vengeance
\f0\i0 ). We evaluated three conditions against the baseline: 
\f2\i Targeted Evolution
\f0\i0  (2 agents), 
\f2\i Full Evolution
\f0\i0  (all 6 agents), and 
\f2\i Asymmetrical Evolution
\f0\i0  (Thorne only).\

