\f1\b Finding 1: System Recovery
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 Full Evolution
\f0\i0  completely cured the monotonic degradation, resulting in a mean valid arc score of 0.715. This represents an improvement of +0.047 over the baseline, placing it within -0.006 of the pristine Depth 0 score. The previously guilty agent (Elena), whose obsolete "concealment" objective had anchored her baseline score at a dismal 0.468, experienced a massive recovery to 
\f1\b 0.725
\f0\b0 , proving that "bad arcs" in deterministic systems are often accurate representations of defunct utility vectors.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Finding 2: The Network Dependency of Drama
\f0\b0 \
The 
\f2\i Asymmetrical
\f0\i0  (Thorne-only) condition yielded a critical negative result. Evolving a single agent degraded the mean score to 0.641. More significantly, an unaligned secondary agent (Marcus) failed to produce a valid arc entirely (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 valid_arcs\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : 5/6, Marcus score: \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 null\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ). Evolving the protagonist into an aggressive investigator while leaving his primary antagonist running an obsolete stealth subroutine fractured the ecosystem. The beat grammar acted as a falsification engine, correctly recognizing that this unaligned interaction possessed no valid dramatic topology. This proves that a protagonist cannot maintain a valid structural arc unless the surrounding multi-agent ecosystem adapts to provide coherent resistance.\

\f1\b Finding 3: Emergent Genre Shift
\f0\b0 \
Without altering the hardcoded event-generation rules, updating the utility weights triggered a native shift in the simulation's event distribution. Comparing the Baseline to the Full Evolution condition, information-gathering events plummeted (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 CHAT\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : 24 $\\rightarrow$ 13, \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 REVEAL\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : 2 $\\rightarrow$ 0), while kinetic confrontation spiked (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 CONFLICT\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : 7 $\\rightarrow$ 13, \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 CATASTROPHE\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : 2 $\\rightarrow$ 7). The system natively transitioned from extracting tension via 
\f2\i Information Asymmetry
\f0\i0  to extracting tension via 
\f2\i Kinetic Conflict
\f0\i0 , which the extraction grammar correctly recognized and rewarded.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 6. Discussion and Future Work: The Stance Matrix\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 These findings demonstrate that coordinated goal evolution produces super-linear structural improvement in utility-weighted narrative ecologies. To achieve long-form season orchestration, a computational narrative system must adapt character parameters to shifting epistemologies.\
However, utilizing an LLM to dynamically generate these new numeric utility vectors (float values) on the fly introduces stochastic hallucination, destroying the determinism and balanced utility economy of the simulation layer.\
We propose 
\f1\b The Stance Matrix
\f0\b0 : a discrete state-machine architecture. Successful parameter evolutions (as discovered in Experiment 2) will be formalized as immutable, pre-balanced Python dictionaries (e.g., \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 Stances.THE_CONCEALER\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  vs. \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 Stances.THE_SURVIVOR\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ). In future iterations, the LLM will serve strictly as a semantic classifier. Operating between episodes, it will analyze accumulated "Canon Texture" (somatic and atmospheric details) and output a single categorical key to trigger the deterministic application of the next Stance. This bridges the semantic intuition of Large Language Models with the rigorous mathematical constraint-satisfaction required for deep narrative structure.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 7. Conclusion\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 Monotonic structural degradation in chained generative narratives is not a computational error, but the mathematical measurement of agents refusing to adapt to reality. By proving that deterministic multi-agent simulations are strictly dependent on coordinated goal-ecology, we demonstrate that persistent digital storytelling requires dynamic adaptation. Through coordinated goal evolution, the Lorien engine proves capable of sustaining mathematically rigorous, highly valid dramatic structures across persistent state changes. These findings validate the crystallization paradigm and establish that formal mathematical modeling of shifting multi-agent constraints\'97facilitated by discrete state transitions\'97is a prerequisite for generating coherent, infinite-horizon computational fiction.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
